<Layout
	title="About Jorge Armando Ramírez Díaz"
	description="Academic profile of Jorge Armando Ramírez Díaz, postdoctoral research fellow at the Universidad Autónoma de Querétaro."
	pubDate={new Date('June 1 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		Jorge Armando Ramírez Díaz is a postdoctoral research fellow at the Universidad Autónoma de Querétaro (UAQ), working on artificial intelligence and robotics with a focus on machine learning methods for robotic systems and human-machine interaction.
	</p>

	<p>
		He holds a Ph.D. in Automatic Control from the Centro de Investigación y de Estudios Avanzados del IPN (CINVESTAV-IPN), where he conducted research under the supervision of Professor Wen Yu. His work spans reinforcement learning, imitation learning, supervised learning, and learning from expert demonstrations for robot control.
	</p>

	<p>
		His current research interests include continuous surface EMG-based wrist and hand estimation, system-identification perspectives for human motor intention, reinforcement learning from expert demonstrations, robust multi-agent reinforcement learning, computer vision, vision-language models, and applied artificial intelligence.
	</p>

	<p>
		Jorge is open to academic collaborations in artificial intelligence, robotics, reinforcement learning, human motor intention modeling, and applied machine learning.
	</p>
</Layout>
